<font color="#FF0000">28 YEARS, STILL CAN'T BELIEVE </font><br>
<tt>Wed Feb 12 21:55:06 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
So long ago, it almost seems like just a dream.  Did it really happen?  Was I really there?  I look down at my arm and see the scar where the AK-47 round went through.  I always remember August 13, 1969.  Arizona territory.  Ran into a Regiment of NVA.  Should have zigged when I zagged.  Ouch.  You got to be shitting me.  I actually got hit.  Still can't believe I was ever that young.  Still feel guilty for living.  Still feel ashamed for serving in such a wrong war.  DMT  Platoon leader Delta, 1/7 USMC  
